content:
Hi everyone!

Next week, I'll be hosting an informal virtual meetup for anyone interested in collaborating towards the IMO Grand Challenge and/or AIMO Prize. The main point will be to get people to meet each other. I can start with some show-and-tell of what I've been working on, and we can open the floor for anyone else with something to share.

The meeting will be at 2024-02-29T11:00:00-05:00. For a link to the video chat, see this calendar and in particular this event.
I've posted an invite on the EleutherAI Discord as well. Maybe we can get some good crossover between the communities.
What kind of skills does one need to have for this collaboration?
There are potentially lots of ways to contribute. I encourage you to attend if you think the project sounds interesting, regardless of your prior skills.
PSA: This meeting is starting in 15 mins.

https://meet.google.com/bey-caaj-zbd
I made the meeting "open to join" so that I don't need to manually approve everyone.
15 or so people showed up, and there seemed to be sufficient interest for a follow-up meeting. So I added an event on the calendar for two weeks from now: 2024-03-14T11:00:00-04:00
(Same time slot, because nobody complained about it.)
(because all the people who couldn't make that time slot didn't show up ;-) )
Reminder (because timezones are weird): today's meeting is at 2024-03-14T11:00:00-04:00, which is 2.75 hours from now.
public, not recorded as now, but could consider that in the future
